<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<title>Print calibration ruler</title>
<style>
  @page { size: 8.5in 11in; margin: 0.5in; }
  * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }
  body { font-family: Arial, sans-serif; padding: 20px; background: #fff; color: #000; color-scheme: only light; }
  .ruler { position: relative; height: 0.6in; border: 1px solid #000; width: 6in; margin: 0.3in 0; }
  .tick { position: absolute; bottom: 0; width: 1px; background: #000; }
  .tick.inch { height: 100%; }
  .tick.half { height: 60%; }
  .tick.quarter { height: 35%; }
  .tick-label { position: absolute; top: -1.2em; font-size: 9pt; transform: translateX(-50%); }
  .box { width: 1in; height: 1in; border: 1px solid #000; display: inline-block; margin-right: 0.25in; }
  .print-note { padding: 8px; background: #ffec9e; margin-bottom: 16px; }
  @media print { .print-note { display: none; } }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="print-note">Print at <strong>100% scale</strong> ("Actual size", no shrink-to-fit). Then check with a real ruler. <button onclick="print()">Print</button></div>
<h1>ShopStock print calibration</h1>
<p>The ruler below must measure exactly 6 inches and each box exactly 1 inch square.
If they don't, your browser print dialog is scaling — fix that before printing labels.</p>
<div class="ruler">
  <% for (let i = 0; i <= 24; i++) {
       const pos = i / 4;
       const cls = i % 4 === 0 ? 'inch' : (i % 2 === 0 ? 'half' : 'quarter'); %>
    <div class="tick <%= cls %>" style="left: <%= pos %>in;"></div>
    <% if (i % 4 === 0) { %><span class="tick-label" style="left: <%= pos %>in;"><%= pos %>"</span><% } %>
  <% } %>
</div>
<div>
  <div class="box"></div><div class="box"></div><div class="box"></div>
</div>
</body>
</html>
